      <div class="faq-answer">Disney took on substantial debt during its $71 billion acquisition of 21st Century Fox in 2019. While it has been paying this down, the remaining $42 billion heavily weighs on the equity value in a DCF.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Why use a 9% discount rate?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Disney faces significant structural shifts in media, making it slightly riskier than a pure-play tech monopoly, but its diverse assets (Parks, Cruises) provide a highly stable cash floor. 9% captures this balance appropriately.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is this a buy recommendation?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">No. This is an analytical framework for estimating intrinsic value. Whether to buy depends on your personal risk tolerance, portfolio allocation, time horizon, tax situation, and conviction in the assumptions.</div>
    </details>
